headline: Allstate Closes Sale of One of Health and Benefits' Businesses
summary: ALL exits the Employers Voluntary Benefits business and receives $2 billion from The Standard. The move aims to intensify the company's focus on the well-performing Property-Liability and Protection Services units.

headline: The Standard finalises $2bn deal to buy Allstate’s voluntary benefits arm
summary: The acquisition includes American Heritage Life Insurance Company, which will eventually operate under The Standard brand.
